  "body": "Description\r\n\r\ntesting voluntary-exit with more validators which are created (activated same time). \r\n\r\n1) Tried it with option `--epoch=\"current_epoch\" ` on validator-1 and it works, validator-1 is exited. \r\n2) Tried without option `--epoch=\"current_epoch\" ` on validator-2 (which is still active) and it doesn't work\r\n\r\nExpected behavior: \r\nsuccessfully exiting of validator with default option (without `--epoch=\"current_epoch\"`)\r\n\r\nActual behavior:\r\n```\r\nFailed to submit exit for validator b8a7d8e\r\nInvalid params response from Beacon Node API (url = http://beacon:5051/eth/v1/beacon/pool/voluntary_exits, response = {\"status\":400,\"message\":\"Exit for validator 210225 fails process voluntary exit conditions Specified exit epoch is still in the future.\"}) \r\n```\r\n\r\nSoftware version: \r\nOS Name & Version: Ubuntu 20.04\r\n* Kernel Version: \r\nLinux eth2-test-server 5.4.0-70-generic #78-Ubuntu SMP Fri Mar 19 13:29:52 UTC 2021 x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux\r\n* Docker Version: \r\n```\r\nClient: Docker Engine - Community\r\n Version:           20.10.6\r\n API version:       1.41\r\n Go version:        go1.13.15\r\n Git commit:        370c289\r\n Built:             Fri Apr  9 22:46:01 2021\r\n OS/Arch:           linux/amd64\r\n Context:           default\r\n Experimental:      true\r\n\r\nServer: Docker Engine - Community\r\n Engine:\r\n  Version:          20.10.6\r\n  API version:      1.41 (minimum version 1.12)\r\n  Go version:       go1.13.15\r\n  Git commit:       8728dd2\r\n  Built:            Fri Apr  9 22:44:13 2021\r\n  OS/Arch:          linux/amd64\r\n  Experimental:     false\r\n containerd:\r\n  Version:          1.4.4\r\n  GitCommit:        05f951a3781f4f2c1911b05e61c160e9c30eaa8e\r\n runc:\r\n  Version:          1.0.0-rc93\r\n  GitCommit:        12644e614e25b05da6fd08a38ffa0cfe1903fdec\r\n docker-init:\r\n  Version:          0.19.0\r\n  GitCommit:        de40ad0\r\n```",
